6.10	Ixil_Triangle	Ixil Community	The Ixil Community is a name given to three neighbouring towns in the Quich√© department in the western highlands of Guatemala. These towns are Santa Maria Nebaj, San Juan Cotzal, and San Gaspar Chajul. The area's population is predominantly of Ixil descent. When viewed on a map, the three Ixil towns appear to form a triangle, because of this, is also named "Ixil Triangle".	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b7/Nebaj.JPG/150px-Nebaj.JPG
